<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 3:01PM CDT  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Clark,
south central Garland and central Hot Spring Counties through 330 PM
CDT...
At 301 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
DeGray Lake State Park, or 12 miles south of Hot Springs, moving east
at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lofton...                         DeGray Lake State Park...
Bismarck...                       De Roche...
Pettyview...                      Midway in Hot Spring County...
Red Oak...
This includes Interstate 30 between mile markers 83 and 85.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
